description:
Meta Desi Comics is an independent publishing company that was the brainchild of Akshay Dhar, an avid comic book lover and writer from New Delhi, India.

It was launched with an aim to provide the Indian readers with a wide array of stories and essentially provide something for everyone in one comic book.

With everything from sword and sorcery to superhero action, Meta Desi Comics was set up to provide young comic loving artists and writers with a platform to showcase their work.

Meta Desi launched its first issue called 'Ground Zero-volume 1' at the Comic Con India at New Delhi in February 2013.

Ground Zero is an anthology which has a number of short stories done by various artists.

Volume 1 has one writer and multiple artists including comicvine's own deadpool1109 A.K.A Anant Sagar and domdom A.K.A Sammy Lenker.

Other artists include the talented Abhijeet Kini and Vivek Goel.

Meta Desi Comics launched Volume 2 and 3 of their Ground Zero anthologies over the course of 2014.

In 2015, they teamed up with Chariot Comics in India to become ICBM Comics.

They also launched a standalone issue of their popular Holy Hell series. The sequel to Holy Hell was launched to massive response at Delhi Comic Con 2015.
name: Meta Desi Comics

description:
Paul Sloboda started Fool's Gold Press so he could self-publish his mini comic Salvager Kain in 2006. The first four issues were sold in specialty shops across North America. Every issue consisted of 25 black and white pages. In 2009 the fifth chapter was made in web comic format, finally being able to make the comic in color and providing pages at regular installments for the fans on the new website www.salvagerkain.com. Without further explanation the new episodes stopped on May 24th 2010 about a year after starting the new website.

The Fool's Gold Press website hasn't been updated since 2009.
name: Fool's Gold Press

description:
Xebec is a subsidiary company to I.G. Port which is the holding company to anime studio Production I.G. They produce Japanese anime films and series for television. Their company structure may sound a bit confusing, but their impressive list of titles isn't . They've worked on series such as Love Hina, Super B-Daman and To Love Ra and co-produced a couple of Pokemon movies/mini series. Some of the companies they work for have impressive track records of their own like Capcom and Genko Ltd. From 1996 to 2010 they've also produced six video games, they are best known for their work on the Mega Man series.

The company employs around 100 workers. Their capital is around 10 million yen, their annual business is approximately 1,5 billion yen.
name: XEBEC

deck: The legends of tomorrow forged from the technology of the future
description:
Lion Forge Comics specializes in publishing original and licensed digital titles sold trough Amazon Kindle store and iVerse Media's Comics Plus service. The company produced it's first title in April 2013 and is steadily producing more and more titles.

The companies founding members are:

  • Managing Director - David Steward II
  • Director of Visual Development - Carl Reed
  • Art Director - Lorenzo Lizana

The biggest news from Lion Forge Comics came at Comic Con International 2013 where they announced licensed comics based on old NBC Universal properties like Miami Vice, Knight Rider, Airwolf, Punky Brewster and Saved by the Bell.

They've also formed partnerships with Rampage Jackson (Rampage Jackson: Street Soldier), actor Flex Alexander (The Joshua Run) and Playmate Claire Sinclair (Wonderous) to produce superhero books based on their likeness and working with them to get their real-life personalities transferred to the comic book pages.

Although licensed titles are a bit piece of their strategy they've also got room for original titles:

  • Bulletproof Knight
  • Catalyst Prime (2013)
  • Roboy
  • Robyn Hood
  • Sorority: Evea

The main focus is on digital printing, but there are plans for going to paper. First plan is to release one complete 8 issue series, perhaps as early as late in 2014.
name: Lion Forge Comics

deck: Self publishing home of T. Warren Montgomery
description:
Will Lill Comics is named after the parents of T. Warren Montgomery (Willie and Lillian). Its main function is to self publish works by comic book artist/letterer T. Warren Montgomery. The first title 'Monty's World' came out in January 2013 and was the first in a 4 issue black and white mini-series.

T. Warren Montgomery has worked for: Boneyard Press, London Night Studios, Brainstorm, Bluewater Productions, Surprising Comics, Red Leaf Comics. Titles include: Razor, Razor/Dark Angel: The Final Nail, Flowers on the Razorwire, Vamperotica, The Blackstone Chronicles, The Mis-Adventures of Adam West, The Leaf and more.

Assisting T. Warren in this venture are writers Jonathan Gilbert & John Helmer and artists Ron Stewart and Luis Rivera.

Printed series currently (dec, 2013) out:

  • Grafix Chronicles (2013), 1 issue
  • Monty's World (2013), 2 issues
  • Monty's World, Dartmann Special (2013), 1 issue
name: Will Lill Comics

description:
Audra Ann Furuichi and Scott Yoshinaga started KimonoKitsy Studios in 2006 after they co-created nemu*nemu (pronounced "NEH-moo", which is based on the Japanese word for "sleepy","nemui / 眠い").

The webcomic is about three magical stuffed puppies: Anpan, Nemu & Enchilada and their two owners Kana and Anise.

Audra is the comic artist, while Scott co-writes and keeps the website updated. They produce new web comics every Monday, Wednesday and Friday. They have produced a nemu*nemu iPhone app and several YouTube video's about making the comic. Nemu*nemu has featured in the East Oahu Sun (2008-2011) and a spin-off comic series called 'Blue Hawaii' is featured in the Honolulu Star-Advertiser on rotating Sundays (2012-present).
name: KimonoKitsy Studios
